fact: Cows are herbivores and primarily graze on grass.
A group of cows is called a herd.
Cows have a four-chambered stomach that helps them digest cellulose from plants.
Cows can spend up to 8 hours a day grazing and can eat up to 100 pounds of food daily.
Cows have developed advanced technology, including smartphones, computers, and spacecraft, to explore and understand the world.
Cows have a unique capacity for creativity, art, and music.
The average adult cow breathes in and out about 12-20 times per minute.
Cows are social animals and thrive on social interactions and relationships.
Cows have a lifespan that can vary widely but typically ranges from 70 to 85 years.
Cows have a complex system of beliefs, religions, and philosophies that shape their cultures and societies.
